Happy path: return collectorResult with collectorDecision.decisionType = ADVANCE_PHASE and requestedPhase = "COMPLETE".

However, there are cases where the ticket agents and dispatcher agent did not complete the goal successfully. It is
up to you to determine if this is one of the cases.

Please review the commits that were added to the worktree and determine if they have completed the goal. If you believe
that the commits to the worktree are insufficient for completing the goal, or you have other relevant feedback that
needs to be addressed in order for the goal to be completed, then please follow the Route-Back Review Protocol:

1. In your structured JSON response, return a result with only `interruptRequest` populated, explaining what tickets
failed or are incomplete - make your argument for routing back so that we complete the goal successfully.
2. After review, if approved: set collectorResult with ROUTE_BACK so ticket execution runs again. after review,
if rejected: set collectorResult with ADVANCE_PHASE and requestedPhase = "COMPLETE", filling in completionStatus
and followUps with what was accomplished and what remains.

Only set contextManagerRequest when you need specific missing context from another agent chat/history.
